http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98Manipal-Surgery-Clinifest%E2%80%99-from-today/article13987286.ece

Kasturba Medical College (KMC) will organise a ‘Manipal Surgery Clinifest 2016’ here from January 8 to 10.It is aimed at enhancing the skills of surgeons and postgraduates pursuing MS/DNB in general surgery.LecturesIn a press release issued here on Thursday, Ramachandra, Head of the Department of General Surgery, KMC, said that the programme would comprehensively cover lectures, symposia and clinical case discussions about topics on general surgery.Eminent surgeons would participate. H.S. Ballal, Pro-Chancellor of Manipal University, would inaugurate the conference.H. Vinod Bhat, Vice-Chancellor, would be the guest of honour, while Poornima Baliga, Dean of Kasturba Medical College, would preside over it, the release added.